<recipe>
	<name>Guacamole Dressing</name>
	<yield_count>8</yield_count>
	<yield_measure>servings</yield_measure>
	<notes>So, like, I had this in my back pocket for a -long- time, believing it the whole while a damned -lie-.  It certainly could not be any good.

Well, Hilary who usually will only politely consume my various experiments in dressing actually went back for SECONDS!  In the same sitting!</notes>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>garlic</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>split</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>avocados</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>peeled and sliced</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>small onion</ingredient_name>
			<preparation>finely diced</preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 clove</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>small tomato</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>2-4 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>diced green chiles (poblanos)</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1 tsp</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>salt</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>1/2 cup</quantity>
			<ingredient_name>mayonnaise</ingredient_name>
			<preparation></preparation>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<preparation>Rub a bowl with the garlic and the mash avocados in engarlicked bowl.  Mix onion, tomato, chiles, salt and mayonnaise to a smooth, sauce-like consistency.  Chill and serve.</preparation>
